<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Chou
                                    En-lai</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.2–3</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-18">18 January 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Herewith I am submitting for your reference a list showing attacks being
                            made by government troops on Communist-led troops and areas between 10
                            and 13 January:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows list of thirteen incidents.]</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chou En-lai</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>